[As indicated in the above report, there have been sporadic reports of outbreaks of chikungunya virus infections in several localities in Bangladesh in 2008 and 2011. Interestingly, although avoidance of mosquito bites is recommended by Bangladesh health authorities, which is very good advice for reducing the risk of infection, no mention is made of the need for elimination of vector mosquito breeding sites in and around houses and other buildings to reduce the risk of virus transmission.

ProMED thanks Roland Hubner for sending in this report as well.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map showing the location of Dhaka in Bangladesh can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2443532,38879.
